{"TopicId":182848,"ForumId":104,"TopicTitle":"Questions about rescaling parts and attach nodes","CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-13T17:02:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-13T17:02:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m rescaling some stock parts right now, and my main concern is about the attach nodes lines, which I actually eyeball for now, but I would to know how it works (I believe some X/Y/Z axis things).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfor instance the stock \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 here\u0027s the part stock CFG:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002224xpwYu.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022237\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/24xpwYu.png\u0022 width=\u0022727\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd here my x3 rescaled version:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ubicyXJ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022399\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/ubicyXJ.png\u0022 width=\u0022725\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith this config, I end up in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E with nodes at the correct lenght, but the node size is still the same:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022YkU50nf.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/YkU50nf.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what do I need to change so the node match 1,25m other parts one? (and also, does it matter? I believe yes..)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tonka Crash","CreatedById":189552,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-13T18:35:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223558373\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182848\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221552496564\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what do I need to change so the node match 1,25m other parts one? (and also, does it matter? I believe yes..)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe final number in each node definition\u00A0is the node size, e.g. node_stack_top = 0.0, 0.9804075, 0.0 , 0.0, -1.0, 0.0,\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#e74c3c;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E1\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u0026lt;== That what you\u0027re looking for\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-13T18:37:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=